      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gratefully Received, Suddenly Rescinded</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>SPCA of Westchester chairwoman Deborah Mehne letter on December 31 article on pork barrel projects notes New York State grant for animal shelter has been rescinded</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I read ''Scraping the Bottom of the Albany Pork Barrel'' (Dec. 31) with great interest. The SPCA of Westchester was the grateful recipient of a grant in support of our Humane Law Enforcement division through the generous support of Senator Nicholas A. Spano.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I read ''Scraping the Bottom of the Albany Pork Barrel'' (Dec. 31) with great interest. The SPCA of Westchester was the grateful recipient of a grant in support of our Humane Law Enforcement division through the generous support of Senator Nicholas A. Spano.</p>
        <p>Surprise, surprise -- we recently were informed by the New York State Department of Agriculture and Markets that our grant had been rescinded. Apparently retaliating against the loser is seen as a fair strategy, regardless of the disappointed but deserving constituents.</p>
        <p>Reforming the system to level the playing field so that discretionary spending is equally available within districts and once pledged, cannot be withdrawn, would certainly be a step in the right direction.</p>
        <p>Deborah Mehne  Chairwoman  SPCA of Westchester  Briarcliff Manor</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
